Key Match Events: England bowled out Oman for 47, the lowest total in T20I history
Jos Buttler scored 24 from 8 balls, leading England's chase
Pre-Game Insights: England chose to bowl first, theorizing that they would be in a better position to manage the run rate equation if they were chasing
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed that the tone was set really well by the bowlers who managed to pick up those early wickets and restrict Oman
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's net run-rate that was minus 1.800 before the match is now plus 3.08, ahead of Scotland's plus 2.164
Others: England will now play Namibia on June 16, and their qualification for the Super Eight stage is still dependent on the outcome of the other group match on June 16 between Australia and Scotland
